them down on one page.

00:20:28.590 --> 00:20:32.150
Mr. Write joined the Marine
Corps at age 17 in 1957.

00:20:32.150 --> 00:20:34.100
He served three years and
then became the first member

00:20:34.100 --> 00:20:37.000
of his family to
graduate from college.

00:20:37.000 --> 00:20:39.220
He went on to earn a
PhD in American History

00:20:39.220 --> 00:20:42.900
and joined the faculty at
Dartmouth College in 1969.

00:20:42.900 --> 00:20:46.720
He served from 1998 to 2009
as the president of Dartmouth

00:20:46.720 --> 00:20:48.600
and for the last 14 years,

00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:51.590
he has been working
to support veterans.

00:20:51.590 --> 00:20:53.900
He has been recognized for this
engagement by the secretary

00:20:53.900 --> 00:20:56.950
of the army, the commandant
of the Marine Corps

00:20:56.950 --> 00:21:00.310
and the commander in chief of
the Veterans of Foreign Wars.

00:21:00.310 --> 00:21:03.570
He also has returned to his work
as a historian, publishing books

00:21:03.570 --> 00:21:06.000
that focus on those who serve.

00:21:06.000 --> 00:21:09.780
Those who Have Borne the Battle:
a History of Americas Wars

00:21:09.780 --> 00:21:12.010
and those who Fought
them in 2012.

00:21:12.010 --> 00:21:17.190
And during Vietnam, an American
Generation and its War in 2017.

00:21:17.190 --> 00:21:20.510
It is my great honor to
introduce James Wright.

